CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 29, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Union - Management Cooperation Help Bring Integration - Edgar Rideout, the new driver-salesman for Rieck's had the help of his fellow union members and management as he began work last week... in photo on the right, Charles (Chick) Henry, retail sales manager, shows Mr. Rideout how to handle the book work at the end of a day. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Edgar Rideout and Charles "Chick" Henry seated behind desk with documents, possibly at Rieck Dairy Company
